import React, { useState } from 'react'; import { Link } from 'react-router-dom'; import { searchItems } from '../services/searchService'; import { SEARCH_CONFIG, SEARCH_SETTINGS } from '../config'; const HelpPage = () => { const [searchQuery, setSearchQuery] = useState(''); const [queryType, setQueryType] = useState('simple'); const [fuzzySearch, setFuzzySearch] = useState(false); const [fuzzyLevel, setFuzzyLevel] = useState(1); const [searchFields, setSearchFields] = useState(SEARCH_SETTINGS.SEARCH_FIELDS.join(',')); const [results, setResults] = useState(null); const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false); const [selectedExample, setSelectedExample] = useState(null); const [semanticConfig, setSemanticConfig] = useState('default'); const examples = [ { id: 'simple', name: 'Simple Search', description: 'Basic keyword search across specified fields.', query: 'consultation', queryType: 'simple', fuzzy: false, fields: SEARCH_SETTINGS.SEARCH_FIELDS.join(','), explanation: 'Simple search looks for exact keyword matches in the specified fields. Results are ranked by relevance score.' }, { id: 'fuzzy', name: 'Fuzzy Search', description: 'Search with typo tolerance.', query: 'consultatoin', queryType: 'simple', fuzzy: true, fuzzyLevel: 2, fields: SEARCH_SETTINGS.SEARCH_FIELDS.join(','), explanation: 'Fuzzy search allows for spelling errors or typos. The fuzzy level (1-3) determines how many character edits are allowed. Higher levels are more forgiving but may return less relevant results.' }, { id: 'semantic', name: 'Semantic Search', description: 'AI-powered search that understands meaning.', query: 'treatments for skin conditions', queryType: 'semantic', fuzzy: false, fields: SEARCH_SETTINGS.SEARCH_FIELDS.join(','), explanation: 'Semantic search understands the intent behind your query rather than just matching keywords. It uses AI to understand the meaning of both the query and documents, providing more relevant results even when exact keywords aren\'t present.' }, { id: 'field-specific', name: 'Field-Specific Search', description: 'Target specific fields for more precise results.', query: 'consultation', queryType: 'simple', fuzzy: false, fields: 'Description', explanation: 'By limiting the search to specific fields, you can get more targeted results. This is useful when you know which field should contain your search terms.' }, { id: 'complex', name: 'Complex Query', description: 'Advanced query with operators.', query: 'skin AND (treatment OR therapy)', queryType: 'simple', fuzzy: false, fields: SEARCH_SETTINGS.SEARCH_FIELDS.join(','), explanation: 'Complex queries use logical operators (AND, OR, NOT) and grouping to create precise search conditions. This example finds items that contain "skin" AND either "treatment" OR "therapy".' }, { id: 'wildcard', name: 'Wildcard Search', description: 'Search with partial terms using wildcards.', query: 'consult*', queryType: 'simple', fuzzy: false, fields: SEARCH_SETTINGS.SEARCH_FIELDS.join(','), explanation: 'Wildcard searches use * to match any characters. This is useful for finding variations of a word stem. For example, "consult*" will match "consultation", "consultant", "consulting", etc.' } ]; const loadExample = (example) => { setSelectedExample(example.id); setSearchQuery(example.query); setQueryType(example.queryType); setFuzzySearch(example.fuzzy); if (example.fuzzyLevel) { setFuzzyLevel(example.fuzzyLevel); } setSearchFields(example.fields); }; const handleSearch = async () => { setLoading(true); try { // Prepare selected facets (empty for demo purposes) const selectedFacets = {}; // Prepare fuzzy level const fuzzySearchLevel = fuzzySearch ? fuzzyLevel : 0; // Execute search const response = await searchItems( searchQuery, selectedFacets, 1, // Page number SEARCH_SETTINGS.DEFAULT_SORT, queryType, fuzzySearchLevel, searchFields.split(',') ); setResults(response); } catch (error) { console.error('Search error:', error); } finally { setLoading(false); } }; return (

Azure AI Search API Reference

Key Features

  • Simple Search - Keyword-based search across specified fields
  • Fuzzy Search - Tolerant of spelling errors and typos
  • Semantic Search - AI-powered search that understands meaning and intent
  • Faceted Navigation - Filter results by categories, groups, and other attributes
  • Complex Queries - Support for logical operators (AND, OR, NOT) and grouping
  • Field-Specific Search - Target specific fields for more precise results

Query Syntax

Feature Example Description
Basic Search consultation Simple keyword search
Phrase Search "skin consultation" Exact phrase match
AND Operator skin AND consultation Both terms must be present
OR Operator skin OR consultation Either term must be present
NOT Operator skin NOT consultation First term present, second term absent
Grouping (skin OR dermatology) AND treatment Combines operators with precedence
Wildcard consult* Matches any characters at the end
